Queries

assortment

Description

Assortment

Returns the entire assortment.

Response

Returns an Assortment!

Arguments
Name Description
carType - String
configurationWindow - ConfigurationWindow Default = Current
engine - String
gearbox - String
modelYear - Float!
policy - String!
salesVersion - String
structureWeek - Float

Example

Query
query Assortment(
  $carType: String,
  $configurationWindow: ConfigurationWindow,
  $engine: String,
  $gearbox: String,
  $modelYear: Float!,
  $policy: String!,
  $salesVersion: String,
  $structureWeek: Float
) {
  assortment(
    carType: $carType,
    configurationWindow: $configurationWindow,
    engine: $engine,
    gearbox: $gearbox,
    modelYear: $modelYear,
    policy: $policy,
    salesVersion: $salesVersion,
    structureWeek: $structureWeek
  ) {
    carType
    components {
      carKey
      code
      type
    }
    engine
    gearbox
    modelYear
    salesVersion
    structureWeek
    carTypes {
      carKeys
      carTypes
      code
      content {
        ...ComponentContentWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      featureType
      globalName {
        ...GlobalNameWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      optionType
    }
    colors {
      carKeys
      carTypes
      code
      content {
        ...ComponentContentWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      featureType
      globalName {
        ...GlobalNameWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      optionType
    }
    colours {
      carKeys
      carTypes
      code
      content {
        ...ComponentContentWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      featureType
      globalName {
        ...GlobalNameWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      optionType
    }
    engines {
      carKeys
      carTypes
      code
      content {
        ...ComponentContentWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      featureType
      globalName {
        ...GlobalNameWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      optionType
    }
    features {
      carKeys
      carTypes
      code
      content {
        ...ComponentContentWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      featureType
      globalName {
        ...GlobalNameWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      optionType
    }
    gearboxes {
      carKeys
      carTypes
      code
      content {
        ...ComponentContentWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      featureType
      globalName {
        ...GlobalNameWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      optionType
    }
    marketingCodes {
      carKeys
      carTypes
      code
      content {
        ...ComponentContentWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      featureType
      globalName {
        ...GlobalNameWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      optionType
    }
    options {
      carKeys
      carTypes
      code
      content {
        ...ComponentContentWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      featureType
      globalName {
        ...GlobalNameWithExceptionsFragment
      }
      optionType
    }
    packages {
      carKeys
      carTypes

        ...ComponentContentWithExceptionsFragment

      }

Queries

carByCarKey

Description

Car by CarKey

If you have a carKey and what to extract the information on that, use this query!

Response

Returns a Car!

Arguments
Name Description
carKey - CarKeyInput!

Example

Query
query CarByCarKey($carKey: CarKeyInput!) {
  carByCarKey(carKey: $carKey) {
    carKey
    configuration {
      appliedChange {
        ...RequiredChangeFragment
      }
      car {
        ...CarFragment
      }
      carKey
      components {
        ...CarComponentFragment
      }
      defaultCar {
        ...CarFragment
      }
      errors {
        ...ConfigurationErrorFragment
      }
      offerKey
      token {
        ...ConfigurationTokenFragment
      }
    }
    configurationByPolicy {
      appliedChange {
        ...RequiredChangeFragment
      }
      car {
        ...CarFragment
      }
      carKey
      components {
        ...CarComponentFragment
      }
      defaultCar {
        ...CarFragment
      }
      errors {
        ...ConfigurationErrorFragment
      }
      offerKey
      token {
        ...ConfigurationTokenFragment
      }
    }
    configurationByToken {
      appliedChange {
        ...RequiredChangeFragment
      }
      car {
        ...CarFragment
      }
      carKey
      components {
        ...CarComponentFragment
      }
      defaultCar {
        ...CarFragment
      }
      errors {
        ...ConfigurationErrorFragment
      }
      offerKey
      token {
        ...ConfigurationTokenFragment
      }
    }
    marketConfiguration {
      all {
        ...MarketConfigurationFragment
      }
      cars {
        ...CarListFragment
      }
      client
      current {
        ...MarketConfigurationFragment
      }
      market
      offers {
        ...OfferListFragment

      salesModel
    }
    offerKey
    dataVisibility {
      baseCarKey
      carKey
      price {
        ...CarPriceVisibilityFragment
      }
    }
    efficiencyClassification {
      co2EmissionDetails
      driveLineEFC
      efficiencyClass

Queries

carByToken

Description

Car By Token

The provided token can (currently) be one of the following: [short, long, userFriendly]. Tokens are fetch through configuration, see link for more information how to fetch tokens.

Response

Returns a Car!

Arguments
Name Description
configurationWindow - ConfigurationWindow Default = Current
token - String A short or long token.

Queries

carConfigurationBySpecification

Description

Car Configuration By Specification

Get the configuration of a car, by providing a rough approximation of a car. The omitted fields will be filled in by [backend] in order to provide a valid Car.

Response

Returns a CarConfiguration!

Arguments
Name Description

Queries

preconfigurationsStartingPoint

Use preConfiguredCarsByPolicy query.
Response

Returns an STARTING_POINT_QUERY

Arguments
Name Description
POLICY - String This holds policy id, the last filter that has the possibility of limiting the offer of the NSC/ Partner etc. For more details about policy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Policys-(CCE).aspx
LOCALE - String

Locale is combination of ISO 639-1 langugage code and ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 code,

For example: sv-SE is a swedish locale of Sweden For more details about locale, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Locales-(language---market).aspx

CLIENT - String Client system name that uses preconfigurationsStartingPointQuery
STRUCTURE_WEEK - Int Provide a STRUCTURE_WEEK argument if you want to return PNO12:s surrounding the given structure week. If no STRUCTURE_WEEK is provided the closest structure week based on the current date and time will be used.
STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM - Int Use the STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM argument if you want to explicitly return PNO12:s of the given structure week and future structure weeks. STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM can be used in combination with the STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO argument to get PNO12:s which are in the defined span.
STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO - Int Use the STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO argument if you want to explicitly return PNO12:s up until the given structure week. STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO can be used in combination with the STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM argument to get PNO12:s which are in the defined span.
PRICE_CONFIG_IN - PRICE_CONFIGURATION_INPUT This is used to define price model you want to fetch from CCH. This is optional field For more details about price configuration input, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Price-configuration-in-queries.aspx

Example

Query
query PreconfigurationsStartingPoint(
  $POLICY: String,
  $LOCALE: String,
  $CLIENT: String,
  $STRUCTURE_WEEK: Int,
  $STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM: Int,
  $STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO: Int,
  $PRICE_CONFIG_IN: PRICE_CONFIGURATION_INPUT
) {
  preconfigurationsStartingPoint(
    POLICY: $POLICY,
    LOCALE: $LOCALE,
    CLIENT: $CLIENT,
    STRUCTURE_WEEK: $STRUCTURE_WEEK,
    STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM: $STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM,
    STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO: $STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO,
    PRICE_CONFIG_IN: $PRICE_CONFIG_IN
  ) {
    _states
    _locale
    availableChildren
    children {
      key
      id
      type
      displayNamePrefix
      displayName
      drivelineLongDisplayName
      group
      displayCarData {
        ...CAR_CONFIGURATION_DATAFragment
      }
      modelYears
      prices {
        ...PRICINGFragment
      }
      highlightedFeatures {
        ...FEATUREFragment
      }
      features {
        ...FEATUREFragment
      }
      description
      technicalData {
        ...TECHNICAL_DATAFragment
      }
      availableChildren
      children {
        ...STARTING_POINT_LEVELFragment
      }
      sortOrder
      startingPointMedia {
        ...STARTINGPOINT_MEDIAFragment
      }
      configurationInformation {
        ...CONFIGURATION_INFORMATIONFragment
      }
      pricingDetails {
        ...PRICING_DETAILSFragment
      }
      _energyEfficiency
      _state

Queries

startingpointQuery

Use carsByPolicy query.
Description

This query gives all the possible configurations of a CCE-policy enriched with tons of metadata. The query supports endless of user journey

For more details about starting point query, please refer this link : https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/startingPointQuery.aspx

Response

Returns an STARTING_POINT_QUERY

Arguments
Name Description
POLICY - String This holds policy id, the last filter that has the possibility of limiting the offer of the NSC/ Partner etc. For more details about policy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Policys-(CCE).aspx
PRICE_LIST - String This field is not used in starting point query
PRICE_CONFIG - String This field is not used in starting point query
LANGUAGE - String

Language is combination of ISO 639-1 langugage code and ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 code,

For example: sv-SE is a swedish locale of Sweden. For more details about language, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Locales-(language---market).aspx

LOCALE - String

Locale is combination of ISO 639-1 langugage code and ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 code,

For example: sv-SE is a swedish locale of Sweden For more details about locale, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Locales-(language---market).aspx

PRICE_CONFIG_IN - PRICE_CONFIGURATION_INPUT This is used to define price model you want to fetch from CCH. This is optional field For more details about price configuration input, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Price-configuration-in-queries.aspx
CHANNEL - CHANNEL Channel is an optional field which holds 'CBV' for CbV requests, and 'DEFAULT' for all others
STRUCTURE_WEEK - Int Provide a STRUCTURE_WEEK argument if you want to return PNO12:s surrounding the given structure week. If no STRUCTURE_WEEK is provided the closest structure week based on the current date and time will be used.
STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM - Int Use the STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM argument if you want to explicitly return PNO12:s of the given structure week and future structure weeks. STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM can be used in combination with the STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO argument to get PNO12:s which are in the defined span.
STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO - Int Use the STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO argument if you want to explicitly return PNO12:s up until the given structure week. STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO can be used in combination with the STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM argument to get PNO12:s which are in the defined span.
CLIENT - String Holds client name of the requested system. For VISTA, it should hold vista

Example

Query
query StartingpointQuery(
  $POLICY: String,
  $PRICE_LIST: String,
  $PRICE_CONFIG: String,
  $LANGUAGE: String,
  $LOCALE: String,
  $PRICE_CONFIG_IN: PRICE_CONFIGURATION_INPUT,
  $CHANNEL: CHANNEL,
  $STRUCTURE_WEEK: Int,
  $STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM: Int,
  $STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO: Int,
  $CLIENT: String
) {
  startingpointQuery(
    POLICY: $POLICY,
    PRICE_LIST: $PRICE_LIST,
    PRICE_CONFIG: $PRICE_CONFIG,
    LANGUAGE: $LANGUAGE,
    LOCALE: $LOCALE,
    PRICE_CONFIG_IN: $PRICE_CONFIG_IN,

    STRUCTURE_WEEK: $STRUCTURE_WEEK,
    STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM: $STRUCTURE_WEEK_FROM,
    STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO: $STRUCTURE_WEEK_TO,
    CLIENT: $CLIENT
  ) {
    _states
    _locale
    availableChildren
    children {
      key
      id
      type
      displayNamePrefix
      displayName
      drivelineLongDisplayName
      group
      displayCarData {
        ...CAR_CONFIGURATION_DATAFragment
      }
      modelYears
      prices {
        ...PRICINGFragment
      }
      highlightedFeatures {
        ...FEATUREFragment
      }
      features {
        ...FEATUREFragment
      }
      description

        ...TECHNICAL_DATAFragment
      }
      availableChildren
      children {
        ...STARTING_POINT_LEVELFragment
      }

        ...STARTINGPOINT_MEDIAFragment
      }

        ...CONFIGURATION_INFORMATIONFragment

        ...PRICING_DETAILSFragment
      }
      _energyEfficiency
      _state
      _priceConfigInput
      _locale
      _states
      priceSummary {
        ...CarPriceSummaryFragment
      }

        ...CarFragment
      }

    sortedOnPrice {
      _states
      _locale

        ...STARTING_POINT_LEVELFragment
      }
      sortedOnPrice {
        ...STARTING_POINT_QUERYFragment
      }
    }
  }
}

Queries

tokenConfigurationDetailsQuery

Use carByToken query.
Response

Returns an CONFIGURATION_DETAILS_QUERY

Arguments
Name Description
PRICE_CONFIG_IN - PRICE_CONFIGURATION_INPUT This is used to define price model you want to fetch from CCH. This is optional field For more details about price configuration input, please refer this link: [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Price-configuration-in-queries.aspx
LOCALE - String!

Locale is combination of ISO 639-1 langugage code and ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 code,

For example: sv-SE is a swedish locale of Sweden For more details about locale, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Locales-(language---market).aspx

TOKEN - String! Car token of configuration selected.
For more details about car token, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Car%20token.aspx
COMPONENT_BEHAVIOR - COMPONENT_BEHAVIOR Component behavior - showAll (default), hideIncluded, hideInPackage
URL - String

Queries

tokenConfigurationQuery

Use carByToken query.
Response

Returns an DATA

Arguments
Name Description
PRICE_CONFIG_IN - PRICE_CONFIGURATION_INPUT This is used to define price model you want to fetch from CCH. This is optional field For more details about price configuration input, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Price-configuration-in-queries.aspx
LOCALE - String!

Locale is combination of ISO 639-1 langugage code and ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 code,

For example: sv-SE is a swedish locale of Sweden For more details about locale, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Locales-(language---market).aspx

TOKEN - String! Car token of configuration selected. For more details about car token, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Car%20token.aspx
COMPONENT_BEHAVIOR - COMPONENT_BEHAVIOR Component behavior - showAll (default), hideIncluded, hideInPackage
CONFIGURATION_WINDOW - CONFIGURATION_WINDOW This enum is used to decide what kind of components to be published. Current(Default one), Future, Past, FuturePast
CLIENT - String Holds client name of the requested system. For VISTA, it should hold vista

Example

Queries

tokenGeneratorQuery

Use carByToken{configurationByPolicy(...)}
Description

Generates a token based on the provided PNO34 data

Response

Returns an TOKEN_CHANGE

Arguments
Name Description
POLICY - String This holds policy id, the last filter that has the possibility of limiting the offer of the NSC/ Partner etc. For more details about policy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Policys-(CCE).aspx
CONFIG - TOKEN_GENERATOR_INPUT! Represents the configuration (PNO34+) which to generate a token for
LOCALE - String!

Locale is combination of ISO 639-1 language code and ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 code,

For example: sv-SE is a swedish locale of Sweden For more details about locale, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Locales-(language---market).aspx

PRICE_CONFIG_IN - PRICE_CONFIGURATION_INPUT This is used to define price model you want to fetch from CCH. This is optional field For more details about price configuration input, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Price-configuration-in-queries.aspx
CONFIGURATION_WINDOW - CONFIGURATION_WINDOW This enum is used to decide what kind of components to be published. Current(Default one), Future, Past, FuturePast
CLIENT - String Holds client name of the requested system. For VISTA, it shoudl hold vista
SELECTION_STRATEGY - SELECTION_STRATEGY This is used to decide what should be kept in selections of state; Enum has two values - allSelected, fullPackageContent and noPackageContent

Example

Query
query TokenGeneratorQuery(
  $POLICY: String,
  $CONFIG: TOKEN_GENERATOR_INPUT!,
  $LOCALE: String!,
  $PRICE_CONFIG_IN: PRICE_CONFIGURATION_INPUT,

  $SELECTION_STRATEGY: SELECTION_STRATEGY
) {

    POLICY: $POLICY,

Queries

tokenTransferQuery

Old CCH Query, use carByToken{configurationByPolicy(...)}.
Description

Transfers from one token to another.

Response

Returns an TOKEN_CHANGE

Arguments
Name Description
FROM_TOKEN - String! Represents the token which to transfer from
TO_TOKEN - String! Represents the token which to transfer to
LOCALE - String!

Locale is combination of ISO 639-1 language code and ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 code,

For example: sv-SE is a swedish locale of Sweden For more details about locale, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Locales-(language---market).aspx

PRICE_CONFIG_IN - PRICE_CONFIGURATION_INPUT This is used to define price model you want to fetch from CCH. This is optional field For more details about price configuration input, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Price-configuration-in-queries.aspx

Arguments

Example

Query
mutation FlushCasApiCache(
  $endpoint: CasEndPoints!,
  $modelYear: String,
  $pno3: String,
  $structureWeek: String
) {
  flushCasApiCache(
    endpoint: $endpoint,
    modelYear: $modelYear,
    pno3: $pno3,
    structureWeek: $structureWeek
  ) {
    count
    pattern
  }
}

Types

BODY

Fields
Field Name Description
name - String Code of the component
language - String This field is not used
structureWeek - Int Structure week start of the component
pno34Plus - String Pno34 Plus that contains Market, model year and Pno34 including standard wheel/ selected wheel option, accessories, packs For more details about Pno34Plus, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/PNO34+.aspx
modelYear - Int Model year of configuration
marketingCode - Int Marketing code
type - String Type of component - for example COL for color
price - Float Price of the component
relativePrice - Float Relative price of the component (diff calculated based on current selection)
text - String This field is not used
pno12 - String This field is not used
available - Boolean To hold the available state. True when component is available to select, false otherwise
selected - Boolean To hold the selected state. True when component is selected in configuration already
included - Boolean To hold the included state. True when component is auto-selected due to must rule or component is part of pack etc
required - [DEPENDENT!] Must included component (must rule) will be listed here
requiredExclusively - [DEPENDENT!] To hold the must rule with exchangeable components
group - String This field is not used
category - String Category of the component which is received from SCNG
categorization - CATEGORIZATION Categorization of the component which is received from SCNG
tags - [String!] Tags is defined in SCNG for the component
description - String Long Description of the component
displayName - String Short description of the component
displayType - BODY_DISPLAY_TYPE Display type of the component
usp - [String!] This field is not used
image - String Image url of the component in view-1
image1 - String Image url of the component in view-2
image2 - String Image url of the component in view-3
video1 - String Video url of the component
video2 - String Video url of the component
requiredChanges - [REQUIRED_CHANGES!] The list of changes required when user selects/ deselects the respective component This also has list of the other components added/ removed upon selection of the component Token is given for selection/ deselection
visible - Boolean This defines whether the component is visible or not
missingPrice - Boolean
componentTypeId - String ComponentTypeId holds CPAM component type. For example : Engine - 4, SV- 5 etc
pricing - [PRICING] This hold price information of the component For more details about pricing strategy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Pricing---strategy-to-implementation.aspx
classification - CLASSIFICATION This gives classification (Group/ sub-group) of the component
sort - Int This gives sort order
userSelected - Boolean User selected status. True when the component is user selected
componentPrice - PRICE_DATA This gives component price
forcedBy - FORCED_BY When a component gets included forcefully by package selection, the package code and short diplay name will be shown in this field
partOf - [PART_OF] If this component is part of a another component, such as a package
co2Effect - Boolean Co2 effect of component. This comes only for accessoires currently
optionType - String Option type holds type of option. A-Accessory, L-Local Option, F-Factory Options
casVisualized - Boolean Feature is visualized in CAS
default - Boolean true if the value is in the startingPoint of the car.
_energyEfficiency - String
_state - String
_priceConfigInput - String
_locale - String
Example
{
  "name": "abc123",
  "language": "xyz789",
  "structureWeek": 123,
  "pno34Plus": "xyz789",
  "modelYear": 123,
  "marketingCode": 123,
  "type": "xyz789",
  "price": 987.65,
  "relativePrice": 987.65,
  "text": "abc123",
  "pno12": "xyz789",

  "usp": ["xyz789"],

  "image1": "abc123",

Types

CAR_CONFIGURATION

Fields
Field Name Description
carType - String Car type is a car model or pno3
engine - String Engine code of a selected car configuration
gearbox - String Gearbox code of a selected car configuration
body - String Body code of a selected car configuration
salesVersion - String Sales version code of a selected car configuration
market - String Marketing code of a selected car configuration
steering - String Steering code of a selected car configuration
color - String Color code of a selected car configuration
uph - String Upholsery code of a selected car configuration
sMessage - String S-Message code of a selected car configuration
history - String This field contains options with comma separated
modelYear - Int Model year of a selected car configuration
commercialModelYear - COMMERCIAL_MODEL_YEAR Commercial Model Year
specMarket - String SpecMarket or ProgramMarket of a configurtion
options - [String!] Options code of a selected car configuration
editionOptionCode - String Returns the edition option code if the starting configuration represents an edition car, and returns null if it's not representing an edition car.
packages - [String!] Packages code of a selected car configuration
pno3 - String Pno3 or CarType
pno12 - String Pno12 code which is a combination of carType, Engine, SV, body, gearbox, steering and Marketing code
pno34 - String This is a pure Pno34, first 34 characters of a product string - start from carType till S-Msg
pno34Plus - String Pno34 string that contains market model year, model, pno12, color, uph, options, packs etc. For more details about Pno34Plus, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/PNO34+.aspx
pno34PlusOptions - String Pno34 string that contains pno34 and options, without pack
pno34PlusOptionsWithoutAccessories - String Pno34 string without accessories and pack
preconfigurationName - String Holds preconfiguration name if the state belongs to preconfiguration
Example
{
  "carType": "xyz789",
  "engine": "xyz789",
  "gearbox": "abc123",
  "body": "xyz789",
  "salesVersion": "xyz789",
  "market": "abc123",
  "steering": "xyz789",
  "color": "abc123",
  "uph": "abc123",
  "sMessage": "xyz789",
  "history": "abc123",
  "modelYear": 123,
  "commercialModelYear": COMMERCIAL_MODEL_YEAR,
  "specMarket": "abc123",
  "options": ["xyz789"],
  "editionOptionCode": "xyz789",
  "packages": ["abc123"],
  "pno3": "abc123",
  "pno12": "abc123",
  "pno34": "xyz789",
  "pno34Plus": "abc123",
  "pno34PlusOptions": "xyz789",
  "pno34PlusOptionsWithoutAccessories": "abc123",
  "preconfigurationName": "xyz789"
}
Types

CAR_CONFIGURATION_DATA

Fields
Field Name Description
displayName - String Display name of the starting point level item/ component
modelYear - Int This is not used in starting point query
uspHeader - String This is not used in starting point query
usp - [String!] This contains uspPattern defined in global meta data under TRIM_LEVEL or EDITION or TRIM_LEVEL_EXCEPTION
carConfiguration - String This is not used in starting point query
carConfigurationDecoded - CAR_CONFIGURATION This provides the summary information of configuration data For more details about carConfigurationDecoded, please refer this link : https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/carConfigurationDecoded.aspx
token - String Short token of a configuration which lives for shorter period of time
state - STATE State holds the state of a configuration, like car token etc For more details about state, please refer this link : https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/State.aspx
media - MEDIAS This field holds the interior and exterior image urls whatever received from CAS
Arguments
types - [String]
angles - [Int]
deliveryInformation - DELIVERY_INFORMATION This field is not used in starting point query
Example
{
  "displayName": "xyz789",
  "modelYear": 123,
  "uspHeader": "xyz789",
  "usp": ["abc123"],
  "carConfiguration": "abc123",
  "carConfigurationDecoded": CAR_CONFIGURATION,
  "token": "abc123",
  "state": STATE,
  "media": MEDIAS,
  "deliveryInformation": DELIVERY_INFORMATION
}

Types

COL

Fields
Field Name Description
name - String Code of the component
language - String This field is not used
structureWeek - Int Structure week start of the component
pno34Plus - String Pno34 Plus that contains Market, model year and Pno34 including standard wheel/ selected wheel option, accessories, packs For more details about Pno34Plus, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/PNO34+.aspx
modelYear - Int Model year of configuration
marketingCode - Int Marketing code
type - String Type of component - for example COL for color
price - Float Price of the component
relativePrice - Float Relative price of the component (diff calculated based on current selection)
text - String This field is not used
pno12 - String This field is not used
available - Boolean To hold the available state. True when component is available to select, false otherwise
selected - Boolean To hold the selected state. True when component is selected in configuration already
included - Boolean To hold the included state. True when component is auto-selected due to must rule or component is part of pack etc
required - [DEPENDENT!] Must included component (must rule) will be listed here
requiredExclusively - [DEPENDENT!] To hold the must rule with exchangeable components
group - String This field is not used
category - String Category of the component which is received from SCNG
categorization - CATEGORIZATION Categorization of the component which is received from SCNG
tags - [String!] Tags is defined in SCNG for the component
description - String Long Description of the component
displayName - String Short description of the component
displayType - COL_DISPLAY_TYPE Display type of the component
usp - [String!] This field is not used
image - String Image url of the component in view-1
image1 - String Image url of the component in view-2
image2 - String Image url of the component in view-3
video1 - String Video url of the component
video2 - String Video url of the component
requiredChanges - [REQUIRED_CHANGES!] The list of changes required when user selects/ deselects the respective component This also has list of the other components added/ removed upon selection of the component Token is given for selection/ deselection
visible - Boolean This defines whether the component is visible or not
missingPrice - Boolean
componentTypeId - String ComponentTypeId holds CPAM component type. For example : Engine - 4, SV- 5 etc
pricing - [PRICING] This hold price information of the component For more details about pricing strategy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Pricing---strategy-to-implementation.aspx
classification - CLASSIFICATION This gives classification (Group/ sub-group) of the component
sort - Int This gives sort order
userSelected - Boolean User selected status. True when the component is user selected
componentPrice - PRICE_DATA This gives component price
forcedBy - FORCED_BY When a component gets included forcefully by package selection, the package code and short diplay name will be shown in this field
partOf - [PART_OF] If this component is part of a another component, such as a package
co2Effect - Boolean Co2 effect of component. This comes only for accessoires currently
optionType - String Option type holds type of option. A-Accessory, L-Local Option, F-Factory Options
casVisualized - Boolean Feature is visualized in CAS
default - Boolean true if the value is in the startingPoint of the car.
_energyEfficiency - String
_state - String
_priceConfigInput - String
_locale - String
hex - String
content - ColourContent
Arguments
locale - String

Defaults to the query locale

market - String

Defaults to market part of locale

preview - Boolean

Fetch working copy instead of published
globalName - String
globalShortName - String
Example
{
  "name": "xyz789",
  "language": "xyz789",
  "structureWeek": 123,
  "pno34Plus": "abc123",
  "modelYear": 987,
  "marketingCode": 123,
  "type": "xyz789",
  "price": 123.45,
  "relativePrice": 987.65,
  "text": "abc123",
  "pno12": "xyz789",
  "available": false,
  "selected": false,
  "included": false,
  "required": [DEPENDENT],
  "requiredExclusively": [DEPENDENT],
  "group": "abc123",
  "category": "abc123",
  "categorization": CATEGORIZATION,
  "tags": ["xyz789"],
  "description": "abc123",
  "displayName": "xyz789",
  "displayType": COL_DISPLAY_TYPE,
  "usp": ["abc123"],
  "image": "abc123",
  "image1": "abc123",
  "image2": "abc123",
  "video1": "xyz789",
  "video2": "abc123",
  "requiredChanges": [REQUIRED_CHANGES],
  "visible": true,
  "missingPrice": true,
  "componentTypeId": "xyz789",
  "pricing": [PRICING],
  "classification": CLASSIFICATION,
  "sort": 123,
  "userSelected": false,
  "componentPrice": PRICE_DATA,
  "forcedBy": FORCED_BY,
  "partOf": [PART_OF],
  "co2Effect": false,
  "optionType": "xyz789",
  "casVisualized": true,
  "default": true,
  "_energyEfficiency": "abc123",
  "_state": "abc123",
  "_priceConfigInput": "xyz789",
  "_locale": "xyz789",
  "hex": "xyz789",
  "content": ColourContent,
  "globalName": "xyz789",
  "globalShortName": "abc123"
}
Types

Types

CONFIGURATION_DETAILS_QUERY

Fields
Field Name Description
_state - String
car - Car
PRICE_CONFIG_IN - PRICE_CONFIGURATION_OUTPUT!
LOCALE - String!

Language is combination of ISO 639-1 langugage code and ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 code,

For example: sv-SE is a swedish locale of Sweden
pno34Plus - String Pno34Plus holds the configuration state in a string format - Market+ MY+ Model+ Pno34 + Options + Pack
For more details about Pno34Plus, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/PNO34+.aspx
specMarket - String Specification market or Program Market code
policyUid - String! Unique Policy ID string for policy
startingConfiguration - String! Configuration state at the starting point
structureWeek - Int! Calculated strucure week of the configuration
currentConfiguration - String! The current configuration which changes applied on starting configuration
currentUrl - String Need to check.........
modelYear - Int Model year of the configuration
modelFamily - MODEL_FAMILY! Model family of the configuration
color - COL! Color on the configuration
upholstery - UPH Upholstery on the configuraion
options - [OPT!]! Set of options on the configuration
packages - [PACKAGE!]! Set of packages on the configuration
engine - ENGINE! Engine on the configuration
gearbox - GEARBOX! Gearbox on the configuration
body - BODY! Body on the configuration
salesVersion - SALES_VERSION! Salesversion on the configuration
steering - STEERING! Steering on the configuration
marketingCode - MARKETING_CODE! Marketing code on the configuration
sMessage - S_MESSAGE SMessage on the configuration
prices - [PRICING] Prices field holds price inforamtion of configuration For more details about pricing strategy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Pricing---strategy-to-implementation.aspx
media - MEDIAS Media information such as image url etc reveived from CAS
features - [FEATURE!] Feature belong to selected pno12 from CPAM
standardFeatures - [FEATURE!] Standard features belonging to base configuration
overview - OVERVIEW Overview holds the summary of the configuration
technicalData - TECHNICAL_DATA_DETAILS Technical data received from REDA, SCNG and CPAM For more details about technical data, please refer this link : https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/technicalData.aspx
techincalData - TECHNICAL_DATA_DETAILS
configurationInformation - CONFIGURATION_INFORMATION Configuration information
configurationValidation - CONFIGURATION_VALIDATION Contains information about whether the configuration is valid or not
transferToken - TOKEN_CHANGE Transfers a token to any given (exclusive or in combination) policy, model year, structure week, pno12 and client
Arguments
policy - String
pno12 - String
structureWeek - Int
client - String
modelYear - Int
editionOptionCode - String
selectionStrategy - SELECTION_STRATEGY
Example
{
  "_state": "abc123",
  "car": Car,
  "PRICE_CONFIG_IN": PRICE_CONFIGURATION_OUTPUT,
  "LOCALE": "abc123",
  "pno34Plus": "xyz789",
  "specMarket": "xyz789",

  "startingConfiguration": "abc123",
  "structureWeek": 123,
  "currentConfiguration": "xyz789",

  "modelFamily": MODEL_FAMILY,
  "color": COL,
  "upholstery": UPH,
  "options": [OPT],

Types

CONFIGURATION_INFORMATION_ENTRY

Fields
Field Name Description
key - String Key gives an unique name to a type
displayName - String This gives short description of the given type
description - String This gives long description of the given type
type - String Define various types such as model, family, modelFamily, trimLevel, driveline, seats
value - Float This gives a numeric value of the given type if available
deltaPrice - Float Price difference between the starting and the current configuration
deltaDisplayPrice - String Display price difference between the starting and the current configuration
upgradedFrom - UPGRADED_FROM Information about the starting configuration
Example
{
  "key": "abc123",
  "displayName": "abc123",
  "description": "xyz789",
  "type": "abc123",
  "value": 123.45,
  "deltaPrice": 123.45,
  "deltaDisplayPrice": "abc123",
  "upgradedFrom": UPGRADED_FROM
}

Car

Description

Base for all Car related information in the graph.

Fields
Field Name Description
carKey - CarKey!
configuration - CarConfiguration

Configuration

Configuration should be used when you want to initiate configuration on a car. However, if you already have a token, you should probably user the configurationByToken field instead.

Arguments
configurationWindow - ConfigurationWindow
configurationByPolicy - CarConfiguration!

Configuration by Policy

Initiate a configuration for this car by making it valid in this policy.
Arguments
client - String

Client

configurationWindow - ConfigurationWindow
editionOptionCode - String

Edition option code

fixComponents - Boolean
modelYear - Int

model year to transfer to

pno12 - String

Pno12 to transfer to

policy - String!

A policy.

selectionStrategy - ConfigurationSelectionStrategy

Selection strategy

structureWeek - Int

structure week to transfer to
configurationByToken - CarConfiguration!

Configuration By Token

If you don't have a token, you should probably use configurationByPolicy instead, or just configuration (depends on your context). Some examples can be found link

Arguments
configurationWindow - ConfigurationWindow
token - String!

A short or long token.

price - PriceAmount

relativePrice - PriceAmount Price relative the currently selected mileage

CarPriceSummary

Fields
Field Name Description
all - CarPriceFields All prices of the car
breakDown - CarPriceBreakdown Price breakdown of the car, to get the pricing for the individual components of it.
dueToday - PriceAmount Due today amount
dueTodayWithoutVat - PriceAmount Due today amount without vat, nil if same as dueToday
nonCarProducts - [TransactionPriceTax!] Non car products of the car.
price - PriceAmount Price of the car
priceWithoutTax - PriceAmount Price of the car without tax, nil if same as price
salesModelMetadata - CarSalesModelMetadata
subscriptionPrices - [CarSubscriptionPrice!] The subscription alternatives available
taxes - CarPriceTaxes All taxes that applies to the car.
totalPrice - PriceAmount Total price of the car
totalPriceWithoutTax - PriceAmount Total price of the car without tax, nil if same as total price
transactionBaseTaxes - [TransactionPriceTax!] Transaction base taxes
Example
{
  "all": CarPriceFields,
  "breakDown": CarPriceBreakdown,
  "dueToday": PriceAmount,
  "dueTodayWithoutVat": PriceAmount,
  "nonCarProducts": [TransactionPriceTax],
  "price": PriceAmount,
  "priceWithoutTax": PriceAmount,
  "salesModelMetadata": CarSalesModelMetadata,
  "subscriptionPrices": [CarSubscriptionPrice],
  "taxes": CarPriceTaxes,
  "totalPrice": PriceAmount,
  "totalPriceWithoutTax": PriceAmount,
  "transactionBaseTaxes": [TransactionPriceTax]
}

Types

ENERGY_EFFICIENCY

Fields
Field Name Description
primaryComponent - ENERGY_EFFICIENCY_COMPONENT This holds the component by which the efficiency class calculation is based on. For example Co2 Emission
details - ENERGY_EFFICIENCY_DETAILS This holds the details of energy efficiency details, whether the data is preliminary or not and groups etc.
efficiencyClass - String The acutal calculated efficiency class of a car configured
efficiencyClassBest - String Efficiency class best is calculated based on low co2 or fuel consumption
efficiencyClassWorst - String Efficiency class worst is calculated based on high co2 or fuel consumption
efficiencyClassRange - [String] This holds efficiency class ranges
Example
{
  "primaryComponent": ENERGY_EFFICIENCY_COMPONENT,
  "details": ENERGY_EFFICIENCY_DETAILS,
  "efficiencyClass": "xyz789",
  "efficiencyClassBest": "xyz789",
  "efficiencyClassWorst": "abc123",
  "efficiencyClassRange": ["xyz789"]
}
Types

ENERGY_EFFICIENCY_COMPONENT

Fields
Field Name Description
name - String Display name of the primay component
unit - String Unit of primary component. For example g/km for co2
value - String Actual value of the primary component
description - String Description of the primary component
type - String Type of the primary component
classification - String Classification of the primary component. For example wltp
drivingCycle - String Driving cycle of the primary component. For example total
measurement - MEASUREMENT Measurement based on. For example : co2
Example
{
  "name": "xyz789",
  "unit": "xyz789",
  "value": "xyz789",
  "description": "xyz789",
  "type": "xyz789",
  "classification": "xyz789",
  "drivingCycle": "xyz789",
  "measurement": "co2"
}
Types

ENERGY_EFFICIENCY_DETAILS

Fields
Field Name Description
preTitle - String This field is not used
title - String This field is not used
description - String This field is not used
isPreliminary - Boolean Flag to denote whether the value is preliminary or official
groups - [ENERGY_EFFICIENCY_GROUP] This lists the groups defined in REDA. Wltp and Nedc are the two groups
Example
{
  "preTitle": "abc123",
  "title": "xyz789",
  "description": "abc123",
  "isPreliminary": true,
  "groups": [ENERGY_EFFICIENCY_GROUP]
}

  "label": "abc123",

Types

MARKETING_CODE

Fields
Field Name Description
name - String Code of the component
language - String This field is not used
structureWeek - Int Structure week start of the component
pno34Plus - String Pno34 Plus that contains Market, model year and Pno34 including standard wheel/ selected wheel option, accessories, packs For more details about Pno34Plus, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/PNO34+.aspx
modelYear - Int Model year of configuration
marketingCode - Int Marketing code
type - String Type of component - for example COL for color
price - Float Price of the component
relativePrice - Float Relative price of the component (diff calculated based on current selection)
text - String This field is not used
pno12 - String This field is not used
available - Boolean To hold the available state. True when component is available to select, false otherwise
selected - Boolean To hold the selected state. True when component is selected in configuration already
included - Boolean To hold the included state. True when component is auto-selected due to must rule or component is part of pack etc
required - [DEPENDENT!] Must included component (must rule) will be listed here
requiredExclusively - [DEPENDENT!] To hold the must rule with exchangeable components
group - String This field is not used
category - String Category of the component which is received from SCNG
categorization - CATEGORIZATION Categorization of the component which is received from SCNG
tags - [String!] Tags is defined in SCNG for the component
description - String Long Description of the component
displayName - String Short description of the component
displayType - MARKETING_CODE_DISPLAY_TYPE Display type of the component
usp - [String!] This field is not used
image - String Image url of the component in view-1
image1 - String Image url of the component in view-2
image2 - String Image url of the component in view-3
video1 - String Video url of the component
video2 - String Video url of the component
requiredChanges - [REQUIRED_CHANGES!] The list of changes required when user selects/ deselects the respective component This also has list of the other components added/ removed upon selection of the component Token is given for selection/ deselection
visible - Boolean This defines whether the component is visible or not
missingPrice - Boolean
componentTypeId - String ComponentTypeId holds CPAM component type. For example : Engine - 4, SV- 5 etc
pricing - [PRICING] This hold price information of the component For more details about pricing strategy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Pricing---strategy-to-implementation.aspx
classification - CLASSIFICATION This gives classification (Group/ sub-group) of the component
sort - Int This gives sort order
userSelected - Boolean User selected status. True when the component is user selected
componentPrice - PRICE_DATA This gives component price
forcedBy - FORCED_BY When a component gets included forcefully by package selection, the package code and short diplay name will be shown in this field
partOf - [PART_OF] If this component is part of a another component, such as a package
co2Effect - Boolean Co2 effect of component. This comes only for accessoires currently
optionType - String Option type holds type of option. A-Accessory, L-Local Option, F-Factory Options
casVisualized - Boolean Feature is visualized in CAS
default - Boolean true if the value is in the startingPoint of the car.
_energyEfficiency - String
_state - String
_priceConfigInput - String
_locale - String
Example
{
  "name": "xyz789",
  "language": "abc123",
  "structureWeek": 123,
  "pno34Plus": "abc123",
  "modelYear": 987,
  "marketingCode": 987,
  "type": "xyz789",
  "price": 987.65,
  "relativePrice": 987.65,
  "text": "abc123",
  "pno12": "xyz789",
  "available": true,
  "selected": false,
  "included": false,
  "required": [DEPENDENT],
  "requiredExclusively": [DEPENDENT],
  "group": "xyz789",
  "category": "abc123",
  "categorization": CATEGORIZATION,
  "tags": ["abc123"],
  "description": "xyz789",
  "displayName": "xyz789",
  "displayType": MARKETING_CODE_DISPLAY_TYPE,
  "usp": ["xyz789"],
  "image": "abc123",
  "image1": "xyz789",
  "image2": "xyz789",
  "video1": "xyz789",
  "video2": "abc123",
  "requiredChanges": [REQUIRED_CHANGES],
  "visible": true,
  "missingPrice": true,
  "componentTypeId": "xyz789",
  "pricing": [PRICING],
  "classification": CLASSIFICATION,
  "sort": 987,
  "userSelected": false,
  "componentPrice": PRICE_DATA,
  "forcedBy": FORCED_BY,
  "partOf": [PART_OF],

OPT

Fields
Field Name Description
name - String Code of the component
language - String This field is not used
structureWeek - Int Structure week start of the component
pno34Plus - String Pno34 Plus that contains Market, model year and Pno34 including standard wheel/ selected wheel option, accessories, packs For more details about Pno34Plus, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/PNO34+.aspx
modelYear - Int Model year of configuration
marketingCode - Int Marketing code
type - String Type of component - for example COL for color
price - Float Price of the component
relativePrice - Float Relative price of the component (diff calculated based on current selection)
text - String This field is not used
pno12 - String This field is not used
available - Boolean To hold the available state. True when component is available to select, false otherwise
selected - Boolean To hold the selected state. True when component is selected in configuration already
included - Boolean To hold the included state. True when component is auto-selected due to must rule or component is part of pack etc
required - [DEPENDENT!] Must included component (must rule) will be listed here
requiredExclusively - [DEPENDENT!] To hold the must rule with exchangeable components
group - String This field is not used
category - String Category of the component which is received from SCNG
categorization - CATEGORIZATION Categorization of the component which is received from SCNG
tags - [String!] Tags is defined in SCNG for the component
description - String Long Description of the component
displayName - String Short description of the component
displayType - OPT_DISPLAY_TYPE Display type of the component
usp - [String!] This field is not used
image - String Image url of the component in view-1
image1 - String Image url of the component in view-2
image2 - String Image url of the component in view-3
video1 - String Video url of the component
video2 - String Video url of the component
requiredChanges - [REQUIRED_CHANGES!] The list of changes required when user selects/ deselects the respective component This also has list of the other components added/ removed upon selection of the component Token is given for selection/ deselection
visible - Boolean This defines whether the component is visible or not
missingPrice - Boolean
componentTypeId - String ComponentTypeId holds CPAM component type. For example : Engine - 4, SV- 5 etc
pricing - [PRICING] This hold price information of the component For more details about pricing strategy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Pricing---strategy-to-implementation.aspx
classification - CLASSIFICATION This gives classification (Group/ sub-group) of the component
sort - Int This gives sort order
userSelected - Boolean User selected status. True when the component is user selected
componentPrice - PRICE_DATA This gives component price
forcedBy - FORCED_BY When a component gets included forcefully by package selection, the package code and short diplay name will be shown in this field
partOf - [PART_OF] If this component is part of a another component, such as a package
co2Effect - Boolean Co2 effect of component. This comes only for accessoires currently
optionType - String Option type holds type of option. A-Accessory, L-Local Option, F-Factory Options
casVisualized - Boolean Feature is visualized in CAS
default - Boolean true if the value is in the startingPoint of the car.
_energyEfficiency - String
_state - String
_priceConfigInput - String
_locale - String
content - OptionContent
Arguments
locale - String

Defaults to the query locale

market - String

Defaults to market part of locale

preview - Boolean

Fetch working copy instead of published

globalShortName - String

OVERVIEW

Fields
Field Name Description
parameters - OVERVIEW_WITH_CIS This field is not used
validation - VALIDATION Policy validation
validatedParameters - OVERVIEW_WITH_CIS This field is not used
price - String This field is not used
requiredChanges - REQUIRED_CHANGES This field is not used
Arguments
NAME - String!
TYPE - String!
co2 - CO2 This field is not used
media - MEDIAS This field holds the inerior and exterior image urls whatever received from CAS
pricing - [PRICING!] This field holds pricing details such as price, payment method, pricelist etc. For more details about pricing strategy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Pricing---strategy-to-implementation.aspx
modelFamily - String This field is not used
displayName - String Short description of the starting point - For example XC90-Inscription
energyEfficiency - ENERGY_EFFICIENCY Energy efficiency of the vehicle with best, worst and range etc.
encodedState - String Short token that holds configuration
decodedState - CAR_CONFIGURATION This provides the summary information of configuration data
pno34PlusOptions - String Pno34 + Options as a string
salesModelUsp - [SALES_MODEL_USP!] This contains the offers data for dcom sales model that are received from pricing app - dcom offers api
usp - [String!] This contains uspPattern defined in global meta data for sales version family
fuelType - FUEL_TYPE Fuel type details of the vehicle
gearboxType - GEARBOX_TYPE Gearbox type of the vehicle
driveType - DRIVE_TYPE Drive type of the vehicle
engineType - ENGINE_TYPE Engine type of the vehicle
state - STATE State holds the state of a configuration, like car token etc For more details about state, please refer this link : https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/State.aspx
pricingDetails - PRICING_DETAILS This field holds various price details such as pretax, taxes, vat, price breakdown etc For more details about pricing details, please refer this link : https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Pricing-details.aspx
startingPointPricingDetails - PRICING_DETAILS This field holds various price details for the starting point of this configuration, such as pretax, taxes, vat, price breakdown etc. This is also commonly known as the base price, with prices based on the color and upholstery, as well as no added packages and options, for the starting point of this configuration. The starting point price will include pricing details for PNO12s with 100 percent options/packages.
priceBreakdown - PRICE_BREAKDOWN Gives the price breakdown at each component level For more details about price break down, please refer this link : https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Price.aspx
_energyEfficiency - String
_state - String
_priceConfigInput - String
_locale - String
priceComparison - CompareTwoCarPrices
Arguments
priceConfigInput - CchPriceConfigurationInput
priceSummary - CarPriceSummary
Arguments
priceConfigInput - CchPriceConfigurationInput
details - CarDetails Use car.content on the root instead (for example car.colour.content)
Arguments
locale - String

Defaults to the query locale

market - String

Defaults to market part of locale

preview - Boolean

Fetch working copy instead of published
Example
{
  "parameters": OVERVIEW_WITH_CIS,
  "validation": VALIDATION,

PRICE_CONFIGURATION

Fields
Field Name Description
name - String
active - Boolean
variableReferences - [PRICE_CONFIGURATION_VARIABLE_REF!]
variableValues - [PRICE_CONFIGURATION_VALUE!]
Example
{
  "name": "abc123",
  "active": true,
  "variableReferences": [
    PRICE_CONFIGURATION_VARIABLE_REF
  ],
  "variableValues": [PRICE_CONFIGURATION_VALUE]
}
Types

PRICE_CONFIGURATION_DATE_INPUT

Fields
Input Field Description
modelYear - String

This field holds the model year of the car
carType - String

This field holds the pno3 or carType
date - String

This field holds the taxationDate (the date the tax calculation is based on)
Example
{
  "modelYear": "xyz789",
  "carType": "xyz789",
  "date": "abc123"
}
Types

PRICE_CONFIGURATION_INPUT

Fields
Input Field Description
name - String

This holds the name of the pricing type: default, sub, sub_fixed, no prices. Follow this link ... for more details.
taxation - [PRICE_CONFIGURATION_TAXATION_INPUT!]

User can ask for other taxation dates from URAX by passing in what date you would like per PNO3 + ModelYear of the car
variableReferences - [PRICE_CONFIGURATION_VARIABLE_REFERENCE_INPUT!]

This is where you pass variables for sub and sub_fixed to CCE. All of the values will default to what Financial Options has as default value if it's not defined.
roundingStrategy - ROUNDING_STRATEGY

How prices should be rounded, and if they are rounded. Defaults to always round. This only applies to displayPrices
priceDates - [PRICE_CONFIGURATION_DATE_INPUT!]

User can ask for other pricing dates from date you would like per PNO3 + ModelYear of the car
Example
{
  "name": "abc123",
  "taxation": [PRICE_CONFIGURATION_TAXATION_INPUT],
  "variableReferences": [
    PRICE_CONFIGURATION_VARIABLE_REFERENCE_INPUT
  ],
  "roundingStrategy": "alwaysRound",
  "priceDates": [PRICE_CONFIGURATION_DATE_INPUT]
}
Types

PRICE_CONFIGURATION_OUTPUT

Fields
Field Name Description

taxation - [PRICE_CONFIGURATION_TAXATION_OUTPUT!] Taxation data of configuration
variableReferences - [PRICE_CONFIGURATION_VARIABLE_REFERENCE_OUTPUT!] Variable references

  "name": "abc123",

Types

PRICE_CONFIGURATION_VARIABLE_REFERENCE_INPUT

Fields
Input Field Description
name - String

This holds the key such as i, customerType, contractLength

value - String

This hold the value of respecive keys

  • Mileage in number for key i,
  • b2b or b2c for customerType
  • number of months for contractLength
Example
{
  "name": "xyz789",
  "value": "xyz789"
}
Types

PRICE_CONFIGURATION_VARIABLE_REFERENCE_OUTPUT

Fields
Field Name Description
name - String This holds the key such as i, customerType, contractLength
value - String This hold the value of respecive keys - Mileage in miles for i, b2b or b2c for customerType and number of months for contractLength
Example
{
  "name": "abc123",
  "value": "abc123"
}

PRICE_DATA

Fields
Field Name Description
listPrice - Float Component price with VAT included
msrp - Float MSRP of the component/ configuration
pretax - Float Pretax of the component/ configuration
msrpDisplayPrice - String MSRP price with currency and rounded
pretaxDisplayPrice - String Pretax price with currency and rounded
displayListPrice - String Display price with currency and rounded
relativeBasePrice - Float Relative base price
displayRelativeBasePrice - String Relative base price with currency and rounded
beforeDiscount - Float Price before discount
beforeDiscountDisplayPrice - String Price before discount with currency and rounded
currency - String Currency
paymentMethod - String Payment method - Unit of pricing
relativePretaxBasePrice - Float Pretax relative base price
relativePretaxBaseDisplayPrice - String Pretax relative base price with currency and rounded
listPretaxPrice - Float Component pretax price
listPretaxDisplayPrice - String Component pretax price with currency and rounded
Example
{
  "listPrice": 123.45,
  "msrp": 987.65,
  "pretax": 987.65,
  "msrpDisplayPrice": "xyz789",
  "pretaxDisplayPrice": "abc123",
  "displayListPrice": "abc123",
  "relativeBasePrice": 987.65,
  "displayRelativeBasePrice": "abc123",
  "beforeDiscount": 987.65,
  "beforeDiscountDisplayPrice": "abc123",
  "currency": "abc123",
  "paymentMethod": "xyz789",
  "relativePretaxBasePrice": 123.45,
  "relativePretaxBaseDisplayPrice": "xyz789",
  "listPretaxPrice": 123.45,
  "listPretaxDisplayPrice": "abc123"
}

PRICE_DETAIL_ITEM

Fields
Field Name Description
name - String This is for dueToday. Holds string 'dueToday'
displayName - String This is for dueToday. Holds string 'dueToday'
type - String This is not used
price - Float Checkout gross price
displayPrice - String Checkout gross price with currency and rounded
pretax - Float Checkout net price
pretaxDisplayPrice - String Checkout net price with currency and rounded
vatAmount - Float Checkout VAT Amount
vatAmountDisplayPrice - String Checkout VAT Amount with currency and rounded
Example
{
  "name": "abc123",
  "displayName": "abc123",
  "type": "xyz789",
  "price": 987.65,
  "displayPrice": "xyz789",
  "pretax": 987.65,
  "pretaxDisplayPrice": "xyz789",
  "vatAmount": 123.45,
  "vatAmountDisplayPrice": "xyz789"
}

PRICING

Fields
Field Name Description
currency - String Currency of the configuration
displayCurrency - String Display currency of configuration
price - Float Price of configuration
listPrice - Float This is not used in starting point query
relativePrice - Float Relative price of configuration
relativeBasePrice - Float Relative base price of configuration
value - Float Price of configuration
displayPrice - String Price with currency and rounded
relativeDisplayPrice - String Relative price with currency and rounded
relativeBaseDisplayPrice - String Relative base price with currency and rounded
benefitInKind - Float Benefit in kind - Informational tax delta value
benefitInKindDisplayPrice - String Benefit in kind price with currency and rounded
paymentMethod - PaymentMethod Payment method - direct or monthly
componentPrices - [COMPONENT_PRICE!] Holds the indididual component prices
priceList - String! Pricelist
contractDurationInMonths - Int Contract duration in months for CbV
contractMaxDrivingDistanceKm - Int Contract max driving distance in kilo meters
contractType - String Contract type
customerType - String Customer type - b2b or b2c
pretax - Float Pretax price
pretaxDisplayPrice - String Pretax price with currency and rounded
Example
{
  "currency": "xyz789",
  "displayCurrency": "xyz789",
  "price": 987.65,
  "listPrice": 123.45,
  "relativePrice": 123.45,
  "relativeBasePrice": 987.65,
  "value": 123.45,
  "displayPrice": "abc123",
  "relativeDisplayPrice": "abc123",
  "relativeBaseDisplayPrice": "abc123",
  "benefitInKind": 987.65,
  "benefitInKindDisplayPrice": "xyz789",
  "paymentMethod": "direct",
  "componentPrices": [COMPONENT_PRICE],
  "priceList": "abc123",
  "contractDurationInMonths": 987,
  "contractMaxDrivingDistanceKm": 123,
  "contractType": "xyz789",
  "customerType": "xyz789",
  "pretax": 123.45,
  "pretaxDisplayPrice": "xyz789"
}
Types

PRICING_DETAILS

Fields
Field Name Description
name - String This gives display name of price type from financial options
description - String This gives description of price type from financial options
price - Float Price of the request
msrp - Float Price calculated from URAX for configuration (with tax)
msrpDisplayPrice - String Display MSRP with currency and rounded
msrpExcludingVat - Float Price calculated from URAX for configuration (exlc VAT tax)
msrpExcludingVatDisplayPrice - String Display MSRP excluding Vat with currency and rounded
pretaxMsrp - Float
pretaxMsrpDisplayPrice - String
pretax - Float Price from GPE of configuration (price before tax)
pretaxDisplayPrice - String Display Pretax price with currency and rounded
vatAmount - Float VAT Amount received from URAX
vatAmountDisplayPrice - String Display VAT amount with currency
pretaxMsrpDelta - Float This shows the difference of MSRP and Pretax
pretaxMsrpDeltaDisplayPrice - String Pretax to MSRP difference amount with currency
netTaxAmount - Float netTaxAmount
netTaxAmountDisplayPrice - String netTaxAmount display price
grossTaxAmount - Float grossTaxAmount
grossTaxAmountDisplayPrice - String grossTaxAmount display price
displayPrice - String Display price with currency
relativePrice - Float Relative price of configuration
relativeDisplayPrice - String Relative price with currency
details - PRICING_DETAILS_DETAILS Contains price details
acquisitionTaxes - [PRICING_TAX_ENTRY] Acquisition tax details received from URAX
informationalTaxes - [PRICING_TAX_ENTRY] Informational tax details received from URAX
ownershipTaxes - [PRICING_TAX_ENTRY] Ownership tax details received from URAX
lineItems - [LINE_ITEM] Line item received from Financial Options/ PricingApp
vatPositionTotals - [VAT_POSITION_TOTAL] VAT Position received from URAX
mileage - PARAMETER Mileage - buckets from financial options, including relative prices if selected. If not set in query default is used
contractLength - PARAMETER Contract length buckets from financial options, including relative prices if selected. If not set in query default is used
priceBreakdown - PRICE_BREAKDOWN This give price break down details of configuration selected
dueToday - PRICE_DETAIL_ITEM
priceIncVat - Float Price inclusive VAT, check price if you need price without VAT
priceIncVatDisplayPrice - String This is the display formatted price of priceIncVat
Example
{
  "name": "abc123",
  "description": "abc123",
  "price": 123.45,
  "msrp": 123.45,
  "msrpDisplayPrice": "abc123",
  "msrpExcludingVat": 123.45,
  "msrpExcludingVatDisplayPrice": "xyz789",
  "pretaxMsrp": 123.45,
  "pretaxMsrpDisplayPrice": "xyz789",
  "pretax": 987.65,
  "pretaxDisplayPrice": "abc123",
  "vatAmount": 123.45,
  "vatAmountDisplayPrice": "xyz789",
  "pretaxMsrpDelta": 987.65,
  "pretaxMsrpDeltaDisplayPrice": "xyz789",
  "netTaxAmount": 987.65,
  "netTaxAmountDisplayPrice": "abc123",
  "grossTaxAmount": 987.65,
  "grossTaxAmountDisplayPrice": "abc123",
  "displayPrice": "abc123",
  "relativePrice": 987.65,
  "relativeDisplayPrice": "xyz789",
  "details": PRICING_DETAILS_DETAILS,
  "acquisitionTaxes": [PRICING_TAX_ENTRY],
  "informationalTaxes": [PRICING_TAX_ENTRY],
  "ownershipTaxes": [PRICING_TAX_ENTRY],
  "lineItems": [LINE_ITEM],
  "vatPositionTotals": [VAT_POSITION_TOTAL],
  "mileage": PARAMETER,
  "contractLength": PARAMETER,
  "priceBreakdown": PRICE_BREAKDOWN,
  "dueToday": PRICE_DETAIL_ITEM,
  "priceIncVat": 987.65,
  "priceIncVatDisplayPrice": "abc123"
}

PRICING_TAX_ENTRY

Fields
Field Name Description
amount - Float Amount of acquisition tax or informational tax
name - String Name of tax. For example: Moms
taxId - String Unique Tax ID defined for Tax in URAX
taxVersionId - String Tax version ID
vatPosition - String VAT Position
vatRate - String Rate % of VAT
displayPrice - String Display price with currency and rounded
type - String Type of tax - for example: default
tags - [String]
frequency - String Frequency of the tax
Example
{
  "amount": 987.65,
  "name": "xyz789",
  "taxId": "xyz789",
  "taxVersionId": "xyz789",
  "vatPosition": "xyz789",
  "vatRate": "xyz789",
  "displayPrice": "abc123",
  "type": "xyz789",
  "tags": ["abc123"],
  "frequency": "abc123"
}

REQUIRED_CHANGES

Fields
Field Name Description
selected - COMPONENT! Selected components
token - String Token for the given selection/ deselection
active - Boolean! Active indicator
componentsRemoved - [COMPONENT!] Components that are removed due to the selection/ deselection of respective component
componentsAdded - [COMPONENT!] Components that are added due to the selection/ deselection of respective component
priceDifference - Float Price difference based current selection
pricing - [PRICING] Holds price information For more details about pricing strategy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Pricing---strategy-to-implementation.aspx
state - STATE State that contains long token and other information
_state - String
_energyEfficiency - String
_priceConfigInput - String
_locale - String
_currentState - String
_baseState - String
dataVisibility - CarVisibility!
car - Car
priceSummary - ComponentPriceSummary
Arguments
priceConfigInput - CchPriceConfigurationInput
Example
{
  "selected": COMPONENT,
  "token": "xyz789",
  "active": true,
  "componentsRemoved": [COMPONENT],
  "componentsAdded": [COMPONENT],
  "priceDifference": 123.45,
  "pricing": [PRICING],
  "state": STATE,
  "_state": "xyz789",
  "_energyEfficiency": "xyz789",
  "_priceConfigInput": "xyz789",
  "_locale": "abc123",
  "_currentState": "xyz789",
  "_baseState": "xyz789",
  "dataVisibility": CarVisibility,
  "car": Car,
  "priceSummary": ComponentPriceSummary
}

Types

RequiredChange

Description

Represents the required configuration change, in order to transition to this configuration. SALES_VERSION

Fields
Field Name Description
name - String Code of the component
language - String This field is not used
structureWeek - Int Structure week start of the component
pno34Plus - String Pno34 Plus that contains Market, model year and Pno34 including standard wheel/ selected wheel option, accessories, packs For more details about Pno34Plus, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/PNO34+.aspx
modelYear - Int Model year of configuration
marketingCode - Int Marketing code
type - String Type of component - for example COL for color
price - Float Price of the component
relativePrice - Float Relative price of the component (diff calculated based on current selection)
text - String This field is not used
pno12 - String This field is not used
available - Boolean To hold the available state. True when component is available to select, false otherwise
selected - Boolean To hold the selected state. True when component is selected in configuration already
included - Boolean To hold the included state. True when component is auto-selected due to must rule or component is part of pack etc
required - [DEPENDENT!] Must included component (must rule) will be listed here
requiredExclusively - [DEPENDENT!] To hold the must rule with exchangeable components
group - String This field is not used
category - String Category of the component which is received from SCNG
categorization - CATEGORIZATION Categorization of the component which is received from SCNG
tags - [String!] Tags is defined in SCNG for the component
description - String Long Description of the component
displayName - String Short description of the component
displayType - SALES_VERSION_DISPLAY_TYPE Display type of the component
usp - [String!] This field is not used
image - String Image url of the component in view-1
image1 - String Image url of the component in view-2
image2 - String Image url of the component in view-3
video1 - String Video url of the component
video2 - String Video url of the component
requiredChanges - [REQUIRED_CHANGES!] The list of changes required when user selects/ deselects the respective component This also has list of the other components added/ removed upon selection of the component Token is given for selection/ deselection
visible - Boolean This defines whether the component is visible or not
missingPrice - Boolean
componentTypeId - String ComponentTypeId holds CPAM component type. For example : Engine - 4, SV- 5 etc
pricing - [PRICING] This hold price information of the component For more details about pricing strategy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Pricing---strategy-to-implementation.aspx
classification - CLASSIFICATION This gives classification (Group/ sub-group) of the component
sort - Int This gives sort order
userSelected - Boolean User selected status. True when the component is user selected
componentPrice - PRICE_DATA This gives component price
forcedBy - FORCED_BY When a component gets included forcefully by package selection, the package code and short diplay name will be shown in this field
partOf - [PART_OF] If this component is part of a another component, such as a package
co2Effect - Boolean Co2 effect of component. This comes only for accessoires currently
optionType - String Option type holds type of option. A-Accessory, L-Local Option, F-Factory Options
casVisualized - Boolean Feature is visualized in CAS
default - Boolean true if the value is in the startingPoint of the car.
_energyEfficiency - String
_state - String
_priceConfigInput - String
_locale - String
Example
{
  "name": "xyz789",
  "language": "xyz789",
  "structureWeek": 123,
  "pno34Plus": "xyz789",
  "modelYear": 987,
  "marketingCode": 123,
  "type": "xyz789",
  "price": 987.65,
  "relativePrice": 123.45,
  "text": "xyz789",
  "pno12": "xyz789",
  "available": true,
  "selected": true,
  "included": true,
  "required": [DEPENDENT],
  "requiredExclusively": [DEPENDENT],
  "group": "xyz789",
  "category": "xyz789",
  "categorization": CATEGORIZATION,
  "tags": ["xyz789"],
  "description": "xyz789",
  "displayName": "xyz789",
  "displayType": SALES_VERSION_DISPLAY_TYPE,
  "usp": ["abc123"],
  "image": "xyz789",
  "image1": "abc123",
  "image2": "xyz789",
  "video1": "abc123",
  "video2": "xyz789",
  "requiredChanges": [REQUIRED_CHANGES],
  "visible": true,
  "missingPrice": false,
  "componentTypeId": "abc123",
  "pricing": [PRICING],
  "classification": CLASSIFICATION,
  "sort": 987,
  "userSelected": true,
  "componentPrice": PRICE_DATA,
  "forcedBy": FORCED_BY,
  "partOf": [PART_OF],
  "co2Effect": true,
  "optionType": "abc123",
  "casVisualized": true,
  "default": false,
  "_energyEfficiency": "abc123",
  "_state": "xyz789",
  "_priceConfigInput": "xyz789",
  "_locale": "abc123"
}

STARTING_POINT_LEVEL

Fields
Field Name Description
key - String Key is an unique string created by concatenating key of all of it's parents.
id - String Id holds the unique identification string for the respective item
type - String This is type of the item. Various types are MODEL_FAMILY, MODEL, MODEL_YEAR, FAMILY, SALES_VERSION, DRIVELINE, ENGINE, GEARBOX, CAR_TYPE, SEATS, DRIVE_TYPE, FUEL_TYPE etc.
displayNamePrefix - String This field is not used in starting point query
displayName - String DisplayName is nothing but the short description of an item
drivelineLongDisplayName - String DrivelineLongDisplayName is nothing but the long description of an item
group - String Group holds the group name of the component/ item
displayCarData - CAR_CONFIGURATION_DATA This field shows the consolidated view of all selected items and token etc
modelYears - [Int!] This contains model year of a car
prices - [PRICING!] This field holds pricing details such as price, payment method, pricelist etc. For more details about pricing strategy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Pricing---strategy-to-implementation.aspx
highlightedFeatures - [FEATURE]
Arguments
relative - Boolean
features - [FEATURE]
description - String Description holds the long description of an item
technicalData - [TECHNICAL_DATA!] This field contains the technical data such as fuelType, gearboxType, acceleration etc whatever received from SCNG and WLTP fields received from REDA or weight fields from CPAM For more details about technicl data, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/technicalData.aspx
availableChildren - [String!] This field is not used in starting point query
children - [STARTING_POINT_LEVEL] Nested children can be defined here
Arguments
type - String
id - String
sortOrder - Int This holds the sort order of the item
startingPointMedia - [STARTINGPOINT_MEDIA] This gives the media type and image url whatever received from CAS
configurationInformation - CONFIGURATION_INFORMATION Configuration information provides the abstract data of configuration such as model family, sales version family, seats etc.
pricingDetails - PRICING_DETAILS This field holds various price details such as pretax, taxes, vat, price breakdown etc For more details about pricing details, please refer this link : https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Pricing-details.aspx
_energyEfficiency - String
_state - String
_priceConfigInput - String
_locale - String
_states - [String!]
priceSummary - CarPriceSummary
Arguments
priceConfigInput - CchPriceConfigurationInput
car - Car Car from startingPoint state
Example
{
  "key": "abc123",
  "id": "abc123",
  "type": "xyz789",
  "displayNamePrefix": "xyz789",
  "displayName": "xyz789",
  "drivelineLongDisplayName": "xyz789",
  "group": "xyz789",
  "displayCarData": CAR_CONFIGURATION_DATA,
  "modelYears": [123],
  "prices": [PRICING],
  "highlightedFeatures": [FEATURE],
  "features": [FEATURE],
  "description": "abc123",
  "technicalData": [TECHNICAL_DATA],
  "availableChildren": ["xyz789"],
  "children": [STARTING_POINT_LEVEL],
  "sortOrder": 987,
  "startingPointMedia": [STARTINGPOINT_MEDIA],
  "configurationInformation": CONFIGURATION_INFORMATION,
  "pricingDetails": PRICING_DETAILS,
  "_energyEfficiency": "xyz789",
  "_state": "xyz789",
  "_priceConfigInput": "xyz789",
  "_locale": "xyz789",
  "_states": ["abc123"],
  "priceSummary": CarPriceSummary,
  "car": Car
}

Types

STATE

Fields
Field Name Description
short - String This is short token of a configuration which can live for short time, (few days to few weeks)
token - String

This is usually called as car token or full token which can live until the configuration is valid at CCE.

To know more about car token : please follow this link URL .
userFriendly - String This holds the configuration state when the configuration is started with starting point
startingConfiguration - String
currentConfiguration - String This holds the current configuration state
structureWeek - Int This holds the calculated structure week of a configuration
Example
{
  "short": "abc123",
  "token": "xyz789",
  "userFriendly": "abc123",
  "startingConfiguration": "xyz789",
  "currentConfiguration": "abc123",
  "structureWeek": 987
}

S_MESSAGE

Fields
Field Name Description
name - String Code of the component
language - String This field is not used
structureWeek - Int Structure week start of the component
pno34Plus - String Pno34 Plus that contains Market, model year and Pno34 including standard wheel/ selected wheel option, accessories, packs For more details about Pno34Plus, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/PNO34+.aspx
modelYear - Int Model year of configuration
marketingCode - Int Marketing code
type - String Type of component - for example COL for color
price - Float Price of the component
relativePrice - Float Relative price of the component (diff calculated based on current selection)
text - String This field is not used
pno12 - String This field is not used
available - Boolean To hold the available state. True when component is available to select, false otherwise
selected - Boolean To hold the selected state. True when component is selected in configuration already
included - Boolean To hold the included state. True when component is auto-selected due to must rule or component is part of pack etc
required - [DEPENDENT!] Must included component (must rule) will be listed here
requiredExclusively - [DEPENDENT!] To hold the must rule with exchangeable components
group - String This field is not used
category - String Category of the component which is received from SCNG
categorization - CATEGORIZATION Categorization of the component which is received from SCNG
tags - [String!] Tags is defined in SCNG for the component
description - String Long Description of the component
displayName - String Short description of the component
displayType - S_MESSAGE_DISPLAY_TYPE Display type of the component
usp - [String!] This field is not used
image - String Image url of the component in view-1
image1 - String Image url of the component in view-2
image2 - String Image url of the component in view-3
video1 - String Video url of the component
video2 - String Video url of the component
requiredChanges - [REQUIRED_CHANGES!] The list of changes required when user selects/ deselects the respective component This also has list of the other components added/ removed upon selection of the component Token is given for selection/ deselection
visible - Boolean This defines whether the component is visible or not
missingPrice - Boolean
componentTypeId - String ComponentTypeId holds CPAM component type. For example : Engine - 4, SV- 5 etc
pricing - [PRICING] This hold price information of the component For more details about pricing strategy, please refer this link : [URL] https://intranet.volvocars.net/sites/CCH/SitePages/Pricing---strategy-to-implementation.aspx
classification - CLASSIFICATION This gives classification (Group/ sub-group) of the component
sort - Int This gives sort order
userSelected - Boolean User selected status. True when the component is user selected
componentPrice - PRICE_DATA This gives component price
forcedBy - FORCED_BY When a component gets included forcefully by package selection, the package code and short diplay name will be shown in this field
partOf - [PART_OF] If this component is part of a another component, such as a package
co2Effect - Boolean Co2 effect of component. This comes only for accessoires currently
optionType - String Option type holds type of option. A-Accessory, L-Local Option, F-Factory Options
casVisualized - Boolean Feature is visualized in CAS
default - Boolean true if the value is in the startingPoint of the car.
_energyEfficiency - String
_state - String
_priceConfigInput - String
_locale - String
content - PrismGenericContent
Arguments
locale - String

Defaults to the query locale

market - String

Defaults to market part of locale

preview - Boolean

Fetch working copy instead of published
globalName - String
globalShortName - String
Example
{
  "name": "xyz789",
  "language": "abc123",
  "structureWeek": 123,
  "pno34Plus": "abc123",
  "modelYear": 123,
  "marketingCode": 987,
  "type": "abc123",
  "price": 123.45,
  "relativePrice": 987.65,
  "text": "abc123",
  "pno12": "xyz789",
  "available": true,
  "selected": false,
  "included": true,
  "required": [DEPENDENT],
  "requiredExclusively": [DEPENDENT],
  "group": "xyz789",
  "category": "xyz789",
  "categorization": CATEGORIZATION,
  "tags": ["abc123"],
  "description": "abc123",
  "displayName": "abc123",
  "displayType": S_MESSAGE_DISPLAY_TYPE,
  "usp": ["xyz789"],
  "image": "xyz789",
  "image1": "abc123",
  "image2": "xyz789",
  "video1": "abc123",
  "video2": "abc123",
  "requiredChanges": [REQUIRED_CHANGES],
  "visible": true,
  "missingPrice": true,
  "componentTypeId": "xyz789",
  "pricing": [PRICING],
  "classification": CLASSIFICATION,
  "sort": 123,
  "userSelected": true,
  "componentPrice": PRICE_DATA,
  "forcedBy": FORCED_BY,
  "partOf": [PART_OF],
  "co2Effect": false,
  "optionType": "xyz789",
  "casVisualized": true,
  "default": true,
  "_energyEfficiency": "abc123",
